    "title": "Can I search Radare's help system?",
    "link": "https://reverseengineering.stackexchange.com/questions/19789/can-i-search-radares-help-system",
    "content": "<html><body><div class=\"s-prose js-post-body\" itemprop=\"text\">\n <p>\n  Radare2 seems to have thousands of commands. Is there a way to search all of those commands?\n </p>\n <p>\n  Like let's say I want to find all commands that had\n  <code>\n   rot\n  </code>\n  (for\n  <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ROT13\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">\n   <code>\n    rot13\n   </code>\n  </a>\n  ), is there a method to do this?\n </p>\n</div>\n</body></html>",
    "votes": "2",
    "answers": 2,
